        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:30PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 330 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Sandusky to near Northern Milan to 7 miles
north of Willard. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sandusky, Norwalk, Western Vermilion, Milan, Northern Milan, Wakeman,
Monroeville, Berlin Heights, Bloomingville, Sandusky South,
Birmingham, and Fairview Lanes.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
